Guys,

Hopefully everyone is safe and warm and not negatively impacted by the weather.  Given that the University moved all classes to remote learning, we have to pivot.

Only a few of you submitted your proposals, which means that I won't be able to provide feedback before class tomorrow.  I know that I asked you to record your presentations, but since only three people actually submitted their recordings, we will pivot to presentations tomorrow.

We will meet on Zoom at noon and every students will pitch their project idea to the rest of the class.  Please make sure that your presentations are "elevator pitch style" - in other words, presentations should not be more than 5 minutes.  Since this is a last-minute change, I'm not going to enforce a particular way of organizing your presentation.  As long as you get across your motivation, project description, and why this project may be interesting to others in the class, that should be sufficient.

We will meet on Zoom at the following link: https://pitt.zoom.us/j/6119545767

